	     Johannesburg - A man who allegedly robbed,
raped, and killed an elderly woman in KwaZulu-Natal was arrested in Soweto,
Gauteng police said on Monday. The man, 22, allegedly attacked the woman,
88, in Paulpietersburg last week, said Lieutenant Kay Makhubela. "He ran to Soweto and last night
[Sunday] the police got information about his whereabouts in Diepkloof
hostel," he said. The man was arrested and would be taken
back to KwaZulu-Natal for his court appearance. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  